A construction worker in China has had to undergo emergency surgery after falling and landing on a pile of steel.According to metro.co.uk one of the metal bars impaled into Wu Qiang&#8217;s scrotum and even reached his abdomen.It is reported that Qiang&#8217;s colleagues managed to hold him steady while fire-fighters sawed off part of the 60cm (20 inch) bar,while surgeons spent an hour removing the rest of the bar.Meanwhile Qiang is expected to make a full recovery and should be discharged within a week. Qiang should make a full recovery as, amazingly, there was no damage to his vital organs,his biggest risk now is a post-operation infection, but he is expected to be discharged within a week, metro.co.uk reported.&#8211;TNA Reporter